### Handle IndexedDB Quota Exceeded Errors

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/articles/indexeddb-max-storage-limit.html

Demonstrates how to handle 'QuotaExceededError' when writing data to IndexedDB. It wraps write operations in a try/catch block to detect quota errors and suggests actions like prompting the user to free up space or removing older data. This ensures data integrity and a better user experience when storage limits are reached.

```javascript
try {
  const tx = db.transaction('largeStore', 'readwrite');
  const store = tx.objectStore('largeStore');
  await store.add(hugeData, someKey);
  await tx.done;
} catch (error) {
  if (error.name === 'QuotaExceededError') {
    console.warn('IndexedDB quota exceeded. Cleanup or prompt user to free space.');
    // Optionally remove older data or show a UI hint:
    // removeOldDocuments();
    // displayStorageFullDialog();
  } else {
    // handle other errors
    console.error('IndexedDB write error:', error);
  }
}
```

