### RxDB Key-Compression Example for Document Transformation

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/articles/indexeddb-max-storage-limit.html

This JavaScript example demonstrates how RxDB's key-compression can transform uncompressed JSON documents into a more compact format by shortening field names. This is useful for reducing storage space when dealing with large datasets.

```javascript
const uncompressed = {
  "firstName": "Corrine",
  "lastName": "Ziemann",
  "shoppingCartItems": [
    {
      "productNumber": 29857,
      "amount": 1
    },
    {
      "productNumber": 53409,
      "amount": 6
    }
  ]
};
const compressed = {
  "|e": "Corrine",
  "|g": "Ziemann",
  "|i": [
    {
      "|h": 29857,
      "|b": 1
    },
    {
      "|h": 53409,
      "|b": 6
    }
  ]
};
```

