### Configure RxDB Memory-Mapped Storage Block Size Limit

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-storage-memory-mapped.md

This snippet demonstrates how to configure the `blockSizeLimit` when initializing RxDB's memory-mapped storage. It takes a number representing the maximum documents per block. Dependencies include `getMemoryMappedRxStorage` and potentially other storage adapters like `getRxStorageIndexedDB`.

```typescript
const storage = getMemoryMappedRxStorage({
    blockSizeLimit: 1000,
    storage: getRxStorageIndexedDB()
});
```

