### Create RxDatabase with Filesystem Node Storage

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/rx-storage-filesystem-node.html

This code snippet demonstrates how to create an RxDatabase instance using the Filesystem Node storage plugin. It requires importing `createRxDatabase` from RxDB and `getRxStorageFilesystemNode` from the premium plugin. The storage configuration includes a `basePath` and an optional `inWorker` flag.

```javascript
import {    createRxDatabase} from 'rxdb';import {    getRxStorageFilesystemNode} from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/storage-filesystem-node';const myRxDatabase = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'exampledb',
    storage: getRxStorageFilesystemNode({
        basePath: path.join(__dirname, 'my-database-folder'),
        /**
         * Set inWorker=true if you use this RxStorage
         * together with the WebWorker plugin.
         */
        inWorker: false
    })
});
/* ... */
```

