### Configure Low Latency RxStorage with Memory Mapping and OPFS

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-storage.md

This snippet shows how to configure an RxDB storage that prioritizes low latency for reads and writes by combining memory-mapped storage with OPFS for persistence in the main thread. It avoids workers to minimize inter-thread communication overhead.

```typescript
import { getLocalstorageMetaOptimizerRxStorage } from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/storage-localstorage-meta-optimizer';
import { getMemoryMappedRxStorage } from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/storage-memory-mapped';
import { getRxStorageOPFSMainThread } from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/storage-worker';


const myDatabase = await createRxDatabase({
    storage: getLocalstorageMetaOptimizerRxStorage({
        storage: getMemoryMappedRxStorage({
            storage: getRxStorageOPFSMainThread()
        })
    })
});
```
